  <summary date="2021-01-05T17:31:22Z" status="Reported to House">No President is Above the Law Act of 2020

This bill tolls (i.e., pauses) the statute of limitations for federal criminal offenses that are committed by the President or Vice President prior to or during their term of office. (Currently, most federal criminal offenses have a five-year statute of limitations.)</summary>
